.TH "xilinx_dpdma_terminate_all" 9 "xilinx_dpdma_terminate_all" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xilinx_dpdma_terminate_all \- Terminate the channel and descriptors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xilinx_dpdma_terminate_all
.BI "(struct dma_chan *dchan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dchan" 12
DMA channel
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Pause the channel without waiting for ongoing transfers to complete. Waiting
for completion is performed by \fBxilinx_dpdma_synchronize\fP that will disable
the channel to complete the stop.

All the descriptors associated with the channel that are guaranteed not to
be touched by the hardware. The pending and active descriptor are not
touched, and will be freed either upon completion, or by
\fBxilinx_dpdma_synchronize\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or -ETIMEDOUT if the channel failed to stop.
